@node "History" "History"

      @{b}Version 0.1@{ub}  : - Prototype without GUI
                     - We could know the resource(s) used by executable(s) in a
                       directory

      @{b}Version 0.2@{ub}  : - a GUI written with MUIBuilder © E.Totel and
                       GenCodeC © Billault(s) was added
                     - You can know all the executables that use a resource

      @{b}Version 0.3@{ub}  : - You can know the available resources on your HD
                     - You can delete unused available resources
                     - Version tested by Florent Brun

      @{b}Version 0.4@{ub}  : - Add Load and Save Database
                     - Display the name of the selected item
                     - Bugs find by Florent Brun was fixed

      @{b}Version 0.5@{ub}  : - Add a info box about available resources
                     - You can select old available resouces
                     - You can move (or delete) selected ressources
                     - Tested by RAMSES's members (a french BBS)

      @{b}Version 0.6@{ub}  : - Bugs fixed
                     - Saved file format was modified
                     - Reduce memory used by ResourceManager ©
                     - First released version

      @{b}Version 0.6a@{ub} : - A small bug fixed (in ASCII file, we write
                       "Resources used by rograms")

      @{b}Version 0.7@{ub}  : - Reduce time to scan Available resources
                     - Use an internal function in order to determine
                       resource version (before we used the AmigaDos program
                       Version)
                     - Links are not interpreted as files but are not yet
                       supported (Wait for next version)
                     - Use context menus on list
@endnode

