@node "Load database" "Load database"

      This item lets you load a database previously scanned with Resource
      Manager and saved with @{"Save Database" link "Save database" 0}.
                             
      The file saved contains :
        - The previously scanned executables with their resources lists.
        - The resources used by executables.
        - The avalaible resources on your hard disks with their informations
          (size, version, date, ...).
@endnode

@node "Save database" "Save database"

      This item lets you save the result of a scan in a file. You will be
      able to load this file with the item @{"Load Database" link "Load database" 0}.

      If you want more explanations about this file, see @{"Load Database" link "Load database" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Save as ASCII" "Save as ASCII"

      This item lets you save a database previously scanned with Resource
      Manager in an ASCII file (that's to say easily readable for a human).

      The ASCII file contains :
        - The previously scanned executables with their resources lists.
        - The resources used by executables ordered by category (library,
          device, ...).
        - The avalaible resources on your hard disks with their informations
          (size, version, date, ...) ordered by category.
@endnode

@node "About MUI" "About MUI"

      This item allows you to display MUI about information.
@endnode

@node "About" "About"

      This item allows you to have little information about this program.
@endnode

@node "Quit" "Quit"

      This item lets you quit the program :-(
@endnode

@node "Get available resources" "Get available resources"

      This item lets you scan your hard drive or another drive (CD-Rom, D7,
      Zip, ...) in order to know the available resources. A requester allows
      you to choose which drive you want to scan.

      If you want to know ALL available resources in your computer, you
      have to select all entries.
@endnode

@node "Select unused resources" "Select unused resources"

      This item allows to select the available resources that are not used
      by any programs scanned previously. 

      Then, you can move or remove these resources (they take a lot of
      space on your hard drive). 


      @{b}WARNING@{ub}: you have to know that:
        - You have to scan all your hard drive in order the program knows
          all your programs in your computer.
        - The algorithm for looking for resources is not 100% safe.
@endnode

@node "Select old resources" "Select old resources"

      This item allows you to select obsolete resources. 

      This feature lets you remove or move resources that can be replaced
      by new versions of these resources.
@endnode

@node "Move selected resources" "Move selected resources"

      This item allows you to move the available selected resources in a
      subdirectory called 'UnusedResources' (The parent directory is the
      resource directory).

      A requester allows you to choose:
        - Move all selected resources
        - Move selected resources with confirmation
        - Do not move the current resource
        - Cancel operation
@endnode

@node "Delete selected resources" "Delete selected resources"

      This item allows you to remove the available selected resources.

      A requester allows you to choose:
        - Remove all selected resources
        - Remove selected resources with confirmation
        - Do not remove the current resource
        - Cancel operation
@endnode

@node "Information" "Information"

      This item allows you to display an information window about the current
      selection.

      See @{"Information Window" link "InfoWindow" 0}.
@endnode

@node "Available resources Informatio" "Available resources Information"

      This item allows you to display an information window about available
      resources.

      See @{"Available resources information window" link "AvailRscInfoWindow" 0}
@endnode

@node "InfoWindow" "Fenętre d'information"

      This window displays information about sslected programs or
      resources. 

      If you select one or more programs, this window will display
      the resources' name used by these programs.

      If you select one or more resources, this window will display
      the programs' name that use these resources.
@endnode

@node "AvailRscInfoWindow" "Fenętre d'information ŕ propos des ressources dis"

      This window displays information about available resources.

      @{b}Note :@{ub}
      If you want to have information about available resources, you have to
      scan your hard drive with the item @{"Get available resources" link "Get available resources" 0}.

      There are two parts in the window :
      - A list in wich you can choose what resources you want to examine.
      - A list that displays all occurence of this resource in your hard drive
        with fields as size, name, version and description.
@endnode

@node "MainWindow" "Fenętre principale"

      There are four parts in this window :

      @{fg highlight}Programs part :@{fg text}

      This list displays the @{"executables" link "Getting started" 0} that are on your scanned drives.

      A context menu on this list lets you :
        - 'Start scanning'
        - 'Stop scanning'
        - Have @{"informations" link "InfoWindow" 0} about selected items (item 'Information')

      If you select one program, its name will be displayed in the "Information
      bar".

      @{fg highlight}Resources part :@{fg text}

      This list displays the resources used by your program. You can filter
      the resource type with the cycle gadget.

      A context menu on the used resources list is available and has the same
      behaviour than the context menu on the programs list.

      A context menu on the available resources list lets you :
        - '@{"Get available resources" link "Get available resources" 0}'
        - '@{"Select unused resources" link "Select unused resources" 0}'
        - '@{"Select old resources" link "Select old resources" 0}'
        - '@{"Move selected resources" link "Move selected resources" 0}'
        - '@{"Delete selected resources" link "Delete selected resources" 0}'
        - Have @{"informations" link "InfoWindow" 0} about selected items (item 'Information')
        - Open the '@{"Available resources information" link "AvailRscInfoWindow" 0}' window (item 'Available
          resources information')

      You can select one or more resources in order to know information with
      the @{"Information window" link "InfoWindow" 0} and with the "Information bar".

      @{fg highlight}Information bar :@{fg text}

      This information bar displays context information.
      When scanning, the program displays the scanned directory.
      If you select a program or a resource, this bar will display its name.

      @{fg highlight}Buttons part :@{fg text}

      "Start scanning" allows you the look for programs and ressources used by
      these programs. A requester asking you the directory that you want to
      scan.                  

      "Stop scanning" stop the current scanning.

      "Quit" ... quits ResourcesManager.
@endnode

